claim.claim-text:
1. A wheel axle suspension adapted to suspend an axle body of a wheel axle from a vehicle chassis of a vehicle, said suspension comprising on both sides of the vehicle:
a bearing bracket arranged on the vehicle chassis;
a rigid trailing arm extending in a longitudinal direction of the vehicle, said trailing arm having a resilient bush at a front end by means of which the trailing arm is hingedly connected to said bearing bracket, the trailing arm furthermore having a contact region essentially complementary to a portion of an outer contour of the axle body, where the axle body, in a fitted position, bears directly against the contact region;
a support part opposing said contact region of the trailing arm, said support part being provided with an axle recess for accommodating the axle body, and being provided with a securing arm extending further towards the rear;
a pneumatic spring which is operational between said securing arm and the vehicle chassis, the securing arm being adapted to be secured to the pneumatic spring; and
two equally sized and shaped U-shaped clamping straps, each having a bend portion and two shanks having a male thread and each arranged on an opposite side of the axle body tensioning the support part and the contact region of the trailing arm towards each other against the axle body;
wherein the support part is provided with holes for inserting each of the shanks of said U-shaped clamping straps, and
wherein the trailing arm, at the location of the contact region, is provided with recesses for accommodating said bend portions of said U-shaped clamping straps.

2. A wheel axle suspension adapted to suspend an axle body of a wheel axle from a vehicle chassis of a vehicle, said suspension comprising on both sides of the vehicle:
a bearing bracket arranged on the vehicle chassis;
a rigid trailing arm extending in a longitudinal direction of the vehicle, said trailing arm having a resilient bush at a front end by means of which the trailing arm is hingedly connected to said bearing bracket, the trailing arm furthermore having a contact region essentially complementary to a portion of an outer contour of the axle body, where the axle body, in a fitted position, bears directly against the contact region;
a support part opposing said contact region of the trailing arm, said support part being provided with an axle recess for accommodating the axle body, and being provided with a securing arm extending further towards the rear;
a pneumatic spring which is operational between said securing arm and the vehicle chassis, the securing arm being adapted to be secured to the pneumatic spring; and
two equally sized and shaped U-shaped clamping straps, each having a bend portion and two shanks having a male thread and each arranged on an opposite side of the axle body tensioning the support part and the contact region of the trailing arm towards each other against the axle body;
wherein one of the trailing arm, at the location of the contact region, or the support part is provided with holes for inserting each of the shanks of said U-shaped clamping straps, and wherein the other of the support part or the trailing arm, at the location of the contact region, is provided with recesses for accommodating said bend portions of said U-shaped clamping straps.

3. A wheel axle suspension adapted to suspend an axle body of a wheel axle from a vehicle chassis of a vehicle, said suspension comprising on both sides of the vehicle:
a bearing bracket arranged on the vehicle chassis;
a rigid trailing arm extending in a longitudinal direction of the vehicle, said trailing arm having a resilient bush at a front end by means of which the trailing arm is hingedly connected to said bearing bracket, the trailing arm furthermore having a contact region essentially complementary to a portion of an outer contour of the axle body, where the axle body, in a fitted position, bears directly against the contact region, the trailing arm at the location of the contact region having one or more holes on both sides of the axle body;
a support part opposing said contact region of the trailing arm, said support part being provided with an axle recess for accommodating the axle body, and being provided with a securing arm extending further towards the rear;
tensioning elements tensioning the support part and the contact region of the trailing arm towards each other against the axle body, the tensioning elements having shanks, the holes in the trailing arm being adapted to receive the shanks of the tensioning elements; and
a pneumatic spring which is operational between said securing arm and the vehicle chassis, the securing arm being adapted to be secured to the pneumatic spring.

4. A wheel axle suspension adapted to suspend an axle body of a wheel axle from a vehicle chassis of a vehicle, said suspension comprising on both sides of the vehicle:
a bearing bracket arranged on the vehicle chassis;
a rigid trailing arm extending in a longitudinal direction of the vehicle, said trailing arm having a resilient bush at a front end by means of which the trailing arm is hingedly connected to said bearing bracket, the trailing arm furthermore having a contact region essentially complementary to a portion of an outer contour of the axle body, where the axle body, in a fitted position, bears directly against the contact region;
a support part opposing said contact region of the trailing arm, said support part being provided with an axle recess for accommodating the axle body, said support part being provided with a clamp recess, and being provided with a securing arm extending further towards the rear;
tensioning elements tensioning the support part and the contact region of the trailing arm towards each other against the axle body, at least one of the tensioning elements being a U-shaped clamping strap having a bend portion and two shanks having a male thread, the bend portion being received in the clamp recess; and
a pneumatic spring which is operational between said securing arm and the vehicle chassis, the securing arm being adapted to be secured to the pneumatic spring.

5. A wheel axle suspension adapted to suspend an axle body of a wheel axle from a vehicle chassis of a vehicle, said suspension comprising on both sides of the vehicle:
a bearing bracket which is arranged on the vehicle chassis;
a flexible trailing arm extending in a longitudinal direction of the vehicle, said trailing arm being hingedly connected at a front end to the bearing bracket, the trailing arm having a contact region essentially complementary to a portion of an outer contour of the axle body, where the axle body, in a fitted position, bears directly against the contact region, the trailing arm, at the location of the contact region, being provided with one or more holes on both sides of the axle body;
a support part opposing said contact region of the trailing arm, said support part being provided with an axle recess for accommodating the axle body, and being provided with a securing arm extending further towards the rear;
tensioning elements tensioning the support part and the contact region of the trailing arm towards each other against the axle body, the tensioning elements having shanks adapted for insertion into the trailing arm holes; and
a pneumatic spring which is operational between said securing arm and the vehicle chassis, the securing arm being adapted to be secured to the pneumatic spring.

6. A wheel axle suspension adapted to suspend an axle body of a wheel axle from a vehicle chassis of a vehicle, said suspension comprising on both sides of the vehicle:
a bearing bracket which is arranged on the vehicle chassis;
a flexible trailing arm extending in a longitudinal direction of the vehicle, said trailing arm being hingedly connected at a front end to the bearing bracket, the trailing arm having a contact region essentially complementary to a portion of an outer contour of the axle body, where the axle body, in a fitted position, bears directly against the contact region;
a support part opposing said contact region of the trailing arm, said support part being provided with an axle recess for accommodating the axle body, and being provided with a securing arm extending further towards the rear;
tensioning elements tensioning the support part and the contact region of the trailing arm towards each other against the axle body, the tensioning elements including bolts having a head and a shank; and
a pneumatic spring which is operational between said securing arm and the vehicle chassis, the securing arm being adapted to be secured to the pneumatic spring.

7. A wheel axle suspension adapted to suspend an axle body of a wheel axle from a vehicle chassis of a vehicle, said suspension comprising on both sides of the vehicle:
a bearing bracket which is arranged on the vehicle chassis;
a flexible trailing arm extending in a longitudinal direction of the vehicle, said trailing arm being hingedly connected at a front end to the bearing bracket, the trailing arm having a contact region essentially complementary to a portion of an outer contour of the axle body, where the axle body, in a fitted position, bears directly against the contact region;
a support part opposing said contact region of the trailing arm, said support part being provided with an axle recess for accommodating the axle body, said support part being provided with a clamp recess, and being provided with a securing arm extending further towards the rear;
tensioning elements tensioning the support part and the contact region of the trailing arm towards each other against the axle body, at least one of the tensioning elements being a U-shaped clamping strap having a bend portion and two threaded shanks, the bend portion being received in the clamp recess; and
a pneumatic spring which is operational between said securing arm and the vehicle chassis, the securing arm being adapted to be secured to the pneumatic spring.

8. An assembly for a wheel axle suspension for suspending an axle from a vehicle chassis of a vehicle, comprising:
a trailing arm which, in use, extends in the longitudinal direction of the vehicle and to which the axle can be attached, wherein the trailing arm is adapted to be hingedly connected to a bearing bracket which is attached to the vehicle chassis, which trailing arm has a contact region against which a first axle body having a first outer diameter can bear directly, wherein the contact region is substantially complementary to an outer contour of the first axle body having said first outer diameter;
a support part adapted to oppose the contact region of the trailing arm, which support part is provided with an axle recess for accommodating the axle, and which support part is furthermore provided with a securing arm which, in the fitted position, extends to the rear from the support part, which securing arm is designed so that the underside of a pneumatic spring can be fitted thereto, the top side of the pneumatic spring being attached to the vehicle chassis;
clamping elements for clamping the contact region of the trailing arm and the support part against the first axle body; and
a shell part which can be fitted between the contact region of the trailing arm and a second axle body, which shell part has an outer contact surface which is designed to bear in a fitting manner against the contact region which has a diameter which is adapted to the first diameter and has an inner contact surface which is designed to bear against the second axle body having a second diameter, the second diameter being smaller than the first diameter.
